<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - OIL COOLER and FILTER HOUSING - Installation - Oil Filter Base
        Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="7">
        <title>Oil Filter Base Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f2350917" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/d1306.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 346. Oil filter base assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new gasket set onto the oil filter base.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new oil filter return tube gasket and filter housing to base seal. Coat gaskets
                and seals with clean engine oil.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter base onto oil cooler cover assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350920" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/d13111.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 347. Installing oil filter base bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install five M8 x 23 bolts, and three M6 x 25 bolts into the oil filter base assembly .
                Tighten all bolts to the special torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350922" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/d13110.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 348. EGR cooler coolant supply port cover bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new seal on the EGR cooler coolant supply port cover and secure with two M6 x 25
                bolts. Tighten bolts to the special torque .
            </para>
            <para></para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350919" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/d1356.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 349. Oil filter return tube</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter return tube by pushing in and rotating clockwise to lock in place, while
                aligning hold down tab with bolt hole in oil filter base. Tighten M5 x 18 lock screw to the special
                torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350921" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/d13108.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 350. Oil filter housing mounting bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter housing and four M8 x 75 mounting bolts. Tighten bolts to the standard
                torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650929" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/d1366.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 351. Oil filter and cap</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter onto cap with new seal and thread assembly into oil filter housing.
                Tighten cap to the special torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, add oil to the engine before starting. See Engine Operation and
                    Maintenance Manual for the engine oil and filter service interval. Correct maintenance will prolong
                    service life.
                </para>
                <para>Correct oil viscosity for diesel engines is important for satisfactory operation, especially in
                    cold weather. Follow the chart in the Engine Operation and Maintenance Manual to determine which oil
                    viscosity is best suited for the expected temperature range.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2350924" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd31/d31229.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="352px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 352. Lube Oil Recommendations</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill crankcase with oil. See Operation and Maintenance Manual for correct refill capacity or
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Engine fluids (oil, fuel, and coolant) are a threat to the environment. Recycle or dispose of
                    engine fluids according to local regulations. Never put engine fluids in the trash, on the ground,
                    in sewers or other bodies of water.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start the engine and check for leaks. Fix leaks.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Shut down engine and check engine oil level. Add oil or drain oil as needed to bring oil
                level to the FULL mark on oil level gauge. Do not overfill past the FULL mark.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
